Warning! The following will violate the provisions of the Philippine Fisheries Code of 1998:

 • Fishing without a valid license, authorization or permit
 • Fishing without reporting the catch or misreporting the catch
 • Fishing in a closed area or during a closed season
 • Fishing of prohibited species
 • Fishing with the use of prohibited gear or methods
 • Falsifying, concealing or tampering with vessel markings, identity or registration to conceal vessel identity or lack of registration
 • Concealing, tampering or disposing of evidence relating to an investigation of a violation
 • Assaulting, resisting, intimidating, harassing with law enforcer, or other duly authorized government officer
 • Intentionally tampering with or disabling the vessel monitoring system

 The government will fine those fishermen and companies that will violate this code. Fine will start from about $5,000.00 to more than $45,000,000.00.
